						<summary>

						<p>This is very much damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">133[3] • • • Pushya (= A.D. 1411)</hi> in the reign of the Vijayanagara king • • Oḍeya. It records that when the <hi rend="italic">Mahāpradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Bāchaṇṇa-Oḍeya</hi> was in charge [of <hi rend="bold">Bārakūra-rājya</hi>], <hi rend="bold">Hariyaparasa</hi> and others made a grant of land for a perpetual lamp to the god <hi rend="bold">Kōṭināthadēva</hi> and for the feeding of a fixed number of Brāhmans in the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
